						               													<description>Construction Whist&amp;#10;Thin veneer of theme: players are pyramid builders in ancient Egypt&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Take one deck of cards, remove any jokers.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;- Turn over the top card; of the deck; this is trumps.&amp;#10;- Shuffle the deck&amp;#10;- Deal 13 cards to each player&amp;#10;- Choose a first player for the round&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Each round consists of 13 construction tricks, in which the players bid for raw materials to extend their pyramids. In each phase, perform the following steps:&amp;#10;- turn over two cards from the draw deck&amp;#10;- first player plays a card&amp;#10;- second player follows suit if possible, trumps or discards if not&amp;#10;- the WINNER of the trick &amp;#10;-- MUST extend their pyramids with one of the two cards face-up on the table&amp;#10;-- MAY further extend their pyramid with the card they played&amp;#10;- the LOSER of the trick MUST then extend a pyramid with the other face up card, but can not use the card that they played.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Extending a pyramid.&amp;#10;- Each pyramid consists of a stack of cards in a suit. &amp;#10;- Each card must be played on a card of higher rank, so the numbers gradually descend.&amp;#10;- Each player can only have one pyramid in each suit&amp;#10;- If a player MUST play a card on a pyramid, but can't, then they have to demolish their pyramid and start again with the new card as the base&amp;#10;&amp;#10;At the end of the game, players score points for each pyramid equal to the number of cards in the pyramid squared.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
